<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7296&amp;p=71855#p71855"><![CDATA[
In my experience, 8-10VDC from 800m to 1.5A is fine across the board. The actual Twin adapter is an oddball 7.6VDC, and I've heard that this was due to the voltage requirements of its FDS circuitry, but that's unconfirmed. <br /><br />You can use a standard (original connector) 9VDC Megadrive type PSU on it if you don't have an original Sharp adapter, or one from a Famicom SFC.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4070">Xious</a> — Fri Dec 24, 2010 4:10 am</p><hr />
