<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7296&amp;p=71694#p71694</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7296&amp;p=71694#p71694"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Questions regarding the NES power supply]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7296&amp;p=71694#p71694"><![CDATA[
Yes you can use DC. DC puts less strain on the system because DC adapters have large capacitors in them so less ripple than with the NES' smaller cap.<br /><br />It's safe to use any 9V DC because of the rectifier.<br /><br />Because the NES has a rectifier, the input voltage drops 1.2-1.4V. The 7805 regulator requires ~7V to function so I wouldn't go lower than a 9V supply. With 9V there is quite little power wasted.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Mon Dec 20, 2010 10:24 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
